UI card design spec (short)
Overall: Minimal, no heavy shadows. rounded-xl, border (1px), shadow-none.
Header (CardHeader):
Tinted background with matching border.
Status colors: green (connected), amber (connecting), red (error), gray (default).
No top padding on the card; header sits flush with rounded corners.
Title uses text-base and status-tinted text; optional small description beneath.
Left-aligned icon uses the same status color.
Content (CardContent):
Clean white background.
Standard spacing: px-6 py-4 inside content.
Inputs/buttons use neutral styling; only status-specific elements get color.
Buttons:
Primary action neutral by default; destructive/negative uses red outline.
Loading uses spinner icon; keep label short.
Badges/State chips:
Small badge on the right of header; mirrors status color.
Variants:
Status card: dynamic border and header color per state.
Configuration card: mirrors current status for header/border; body stays neutral.
Accessibility:
Sufficient contrast for tinted headers.
Clear focus styles on interactive elements.
